snippet.textDisplay: I don’t understand his problem with frozen food. When you freeze food, that stops time for it. So it remains suspended in a freshness matrix for as long as you need and then when you unfreeze it, the clock starts again. So if I freeze vegetables 5 minutes after I pick them - leave them frozen for 2 months - then defrost and cook them in 10 minutes - then they’re only 15 minutes since being picked and that makes it fresh by any definition.
snippet.textOriginal: I don’t understand his problem with frozen food. When you freeze food, that stops time for it. So it remains suspended in a freshness matrix for as long as you need and then when you unfreeze it, the clock starts again. So if I freeze vegetables 5 minutes after I pick them - leave them frozen for 2 months - then defrost and cook them in 10 minutes - then they’re only 15 minutes since being picked and that makes it fresh by any definition.
